Mombasa businessman Tahir Sheikh Said popularly known as TSS has died in a South African hospital while undergoing treatment, family saysRecently his sons were involved in a fight for control of his multi-billion-shilling empire. Sabir Tahir Said and his younger brother Sheikh Noorein Twahir are fighting for control of the transport segment of two firms, Transmara Logistic Ltd and TSS Pop Service Stations. TSS was the main shareholder in the two firms. The two brothers had differed on how to share the many lorries their father owns as well as other properties claimed by two companies where they are claiming shares.